The paper focuses on the problem of partitioned multiprocessor scheduling for mixed-criticality systems, which involves real-time scheduling and resource allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also deals with the design of efficient partitioning strategies, which falls under the category of cs.EM (Embedded Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the schedulability performance of the proposed strategies, which is related to cs.RT (Real-Time and Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of resource utilization, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
